    <h1>Clas&#xAD;sics With A Twist</h1>
    <h2></h2>
    <section>
        <a href="/singapore/the-straits-times/textview" title="The Straits Times">The Straits Times</a>
        - <a href="/singapore/the-straits-times/20200906/textview" title="The Straits Times - 2020-09-06"><time>2020-09-06</time></a>
        - <span>LIFE I FEATURES</span>
        - <span role="byline"></span>
    </section>

    <p>The chefs at Wan Hao Chi­nese Restau­rant at Sin­ga­pore Mar­riott Tang Plaza Ho­tel have come up with cre­ative twists to clas­sic moon­cakes. One such cre­ation is the Golden Black Truf­fle Baked Moon­cake with Bay­onne Ham and Sin­gle Yolk ($82 for a box of four), which com­bines the sweet­ness of white lo­tus seed paste with savoury Bay­onne ham and the earthy aroma of black truf­fles. Other in­no­va­tive flavours in­clude snowskin va­ri­eties such as the Rose Tea Snowskin Moon­cake with Cham­pagne Truf­fle ($74 for a box of eight) and Man­darin Orange Snowskin Moon­cake with Caramel Sea Salt Truf­fle ($72 for a box of eight) that will please dessert lovers. To or­der, visit www.cel­e­bra­to­ry­de­lights.com/moon­cakes or call 6831 4708.</p>

